Let’s account for the translation btw. the origins of {A}\{A\} and {B}\{B\}.
𝐭∈ℝ3\bm{t} \in \mathbb{R}^3 is a vector defining the origin of frame {B}\{B\} w.r.t. frame {A}\{A\} and 𝐑\bm{R} is the rotation matrix describing the orientation of the axes of frame {B}\{B\} w.r.t. frame {A}\{A\}. (xayaza1)=[A𝐑B𝐭01×31](xbybzb1)
\begin{pmatrix}
x_a \\ y_a \\ z_a \\ 1
\end{pmatrix} = 
\begin{bmatrix}
